## TOPs XMP Sequence to Frameset XMP

### Example HIP:

* TOPs\_XMP\_Sequence\_to\_Frameset\_XMP\_V001.hip

### Description:

Copy the Reality Capture exported camera pose XMP files from a single frame reconstruction into the numbered frameset folders. This allows the same camera alignment data to be used across a volumetric video sequence.

![][image26]

### TOPs Node Parameters:

#### Range Generate Node

Specify Range As: Value Range  
Value Range: 2-153 ("Right click \> Delete Channels" to unlock the number inputs)  
\[x\] Inclusive  
Store Value as: Custom Attribute  
Attribute Name: rangeValue  
\[x\] Set Range Attribute: range

Note: Set the "End Frame" range value to line up with the number of frames in the image sequence.

![][image27]

#### File Pattern Node

Files Type: Files Only  
Pattern: $HIP/images/0001/\*.xmp

Outputs:  
\[x\] Output Attribute: filesXMP  
\[x\] Output File Tag: file/xmp

![][image28]

#### Attribute from String Node

Source String: \`@filename\`  
Operation: Match by Pattern  
Pattern Type: Simple Pattern  
Pattern: Camera.{ViewName:string}.xmp

![][image29]

#### File Copy Node

Source:  
File Source: Custom File Path  
File path: \`@filesXMP\`  
Destination:  
Copy To: File  
File Path: $HIP/images/\`padzero(4, @rangeValue)\`/Camera.\`@ViewNum\`.xmp  
File Tag: file/xmp

Wait For All Node  
Merge Output Files: All Files
